  "prompt": "I feel sleepy and dull all of the time. What can I do to be energetic all of the time?",
  "response": "Here are some tips to help boost your energy levels:\n\n1. Sleep hygiene\n- Maintain a consistent sleep schedule\n- Get 7-9 hours of quality sleep\n- Create a dark, quiet sleeping environment\n- Avoid screens before bedtime\n\n2. Nutrition\n- Eat a balanced diet with whole foods\n- Stay hydrated\n- Limit sugar and processed foods\n- Eat regular, small meals\n- Include protein, complex carbohydrates, and healthy fats\n\n3. Exercise\n- Regular physical activity\n- Morning or afternoon workouts\n- Mix cardio and strength training\n- Take short walks during the day\n\n4. Stress management\n- Practice meditation\n- Try deep breathing exercises\n- Get regular breaks\n- Practice yoga\n- Consider professional counseling if needed\n\n5. Lifestyle habits\n- Limit caffeine intake\n- Reduce alcohol consumption\n- Quit smoking\n- Maintain social connections\n- Spend time outdoors\n\n6. Medical considerations\n- Check for underlying health conditions\n- Get regular check-ups\n- Test for vitamin deficiencies\n- Consider supplements if recommended by a doctor\n\n7. Mental health\n- Engage in enjoyable activities\n- Maintain a positive outlook\n- Practice gratitude\n\nConsult a healthcare professional if persistent fatigue continues.",
